#: src/configuring-languages.md:404
msgid "Using Theme Extensions"
msgstr ""

#: src/configuring-languages.md:406
msgid ""
"Zed supports theme extensions. Browse and install theme extensions from the "
"Extensions panel (<kbd class=\"keybinding\">cmd-shift-x|ctrl-shift-x</kbd>)."
msgstr ""

#: src/configuring-languages.md:408
msgid ""
"To create your own theme extension, refer to the [Developing Theme "
"Extensions](./extensions/themes.md) guide."
msgstr ""

#: src/configuring-languages.md:410
msgid "Using Language Server Features"
msgstr ""

#: src/configuring-languages.md:412
msgid "Inlay Hints"
msgstr ""

#: src/configuring-languages.md:414
msgid ""
"Inlay hints provide additional information inline in your code, such as "
"parameter names or inferred types. Configure inlay hints in your `settings."
"json`:"
msgstr ""

#: src/configuring-languages.md:417
msgid "\"inlay_hints\""
msgstr ""

#: src/configuring-languages.md:418
msgid "\"enabled\""
msgstr ""

#: src/configuring-languages.md:419
msgid "\"show_type_hints\""
msgstr ""

#: src/configuring-languages.md:420
msgid "\"show_parameter_hints\""
msgstr ""

#: src/configuring-languages.md:421
msgid "\"show_other_hints\""
msgstr ""

#: src/configuring-languages.md:425
msgid ""
"For language-specific inlay hint settings, refer to the documentation for "
"each language."
msgstr ""

#: src/configuring-languages.md:427
msgid "Code Actions"
msgstr ""

#: src/configuring-languages.md:429
msgid ""
"Code actions provide quick fixes and refactoring options. Access code "
"actions using the `editor: Toggle Code Actions` command or by clicking the "
"lightbulb icon that appears next to your cursor when actions are available."
msgstr ""

#: src/configuring-languages.md:431
msgid "Go To Definition and References"
msgstr ""

#: src/configuring-languages.md:433
msgid "Use these commands to navigate your codebase:"
msgstr ""

#: src/configuring-languages.md:435
msgid "`editor: Go to Definition` (<kbd>f12|f12</kbd>)"
msgstr ""

#: src/configuring-languages.md:436
msgid "`editor: Go to Type Definition` (<kbd>cmd-f12|ctrl-f12</kbd>)"
msgstr ""

#: src/configuring-languages.md:437
msgid "`editor: Find All References` (<kbd>shift-f12|shift-f12</kbd>)"
msgstr ""

#: src/configuring-languages.md:439
msgid "Rename Symbol"
msgstr ""

#: src/configuring-languages.md:441
msgid "To rename a symbol across your project:"
msgstr ""

#: src/configuring-languages.md:443
msgid "Place your cursor on the symbol"
msgstr ""

#: src/configuring-languages.md:444
msgid "Use the `editor: Rename Symbol` command (<kbd>f2|f2</kbd>)"
msgstr ""

#: src/configuring-languages.md:445
msgid "Enter the new name and press Enter"
msgstr ""

#: src/configuring-languages.md:447
msgid ""
"These features depend on the capabilities of the language server for each "
"language."
msgstr ""

#: src/configuring-languages.md:449
msgid ""
"When renaming a symbol that spans multiple files, Zed will open a preview in "
"a multibuffer. This allows you to review all the changes across your project "
"before applying them. To confirm the rename, simply save the multibuffer. If "
"you decide not to proceed with the rename, you can undo the changes or close "
"the multibuffer without saving."
msgstr ""

#: src/configuring-languages.md:451
msgid "Hover Information"
msgstr ""

#: src/configuring-languages.md:453
msgid ""
"Use the `editor: Hover` command to display information about the symbol "
"under the cursor. This often includes type information, documentation, and "
"links to relevant resources."
msgstr ""

#: src/configuring-languages.md:455
msgid "Workspace Symbol Search"
msgstr ""

#: src/configuring-languages.md:457
msgid ""
"The `workspace: Open Symbol` command allows you to search for symbols "
"(functions, classes, variables) across your entire project. This is useful "
"for quickly navigating large codebases."
msgstr ""

#: src/configuring-languages.md:459
msgid "Code Completion"
msgstr ""

#: src/configuring-languages.md:461
msgid ""
"Zed provides intelligent code completion suggestions as you type. You can "
"manually trigger completion with the `editor: Show Completions` command. Use "
"<kbd>tab|tab</kbd> or <kbd>enter|enter</kbd> to accept suggestions."
msgstr ""

#: src/configuring-languages.md:463
msgid "Diagnostics"
msgstr ""

#: src/configuring-languages.md:465
msgid ""
"Language servers provide real-time diagnostics (errors, warnings, hints) as "
"you code. View all diagnostics for your project using the `diagnostics: "
"Toggle` command."
msgstr ""
